### Commercial Use and Substantial Usage Clause

If you or your organization makes **substantial use** of this software in a commercial
setting—especially in the context of providing hosted services, embedding it in
proprietary systems, or deriving significant business value from its usage—you are
required to obtain a commercial license from the copyright holder.

"Substantial use" is intentionally left open to interpretation. We trust that
responsible organizations will recognize when they have crossed this threshold.
If in doubt, please reach out and inquire about commercial licensing terms.

Commercial licensing provides:
